  "successionPatrimoineTitle": "Succession & estate planning",
  "successionPatrimoineAlertTitle": "Without a will, your partner inherits NOTHING",
  "successionPatrimoineAlertBody": "Swiss inheritance law (CC art. 457 ff.) first protects descendants, then parents and the legal spouse. Without a legal bond and without a will, a cohabiting partner is excluded from the estate — regardless of the duration of cohabitation.",
  "successionPatrimoineNotionsCles": "Key concepts",
  "successionPatrimoineReservesTitle": "Forced heirship",
  "successionPatrimoineReservesSubtitle": "CC art. 470–471",
  "successionPatrimoineReservesBody": "A portion of your estate is reserved by law for your descendants (1/2 of their legal share) and for your spouse (1/2 of their legal share). This portion cannot be set aside by will, except revocation for ingratitude.",
  "successionPatrimoineQuotiteTitle": "Disposable portion",
  "successionPatrimoineQuotiteSubtitle": "CC art. 470 para. 2",
  "successionPatrimoineQuotiteBody": "What remains after forced heirship is your \"disposable portion\" — the share you can freely bequeath to anyone: unmarried partner, friends, associations. If you have children, your disposable portion is 1/2 of your estate.",
  "successionPatrimoineTestamentTitle": "Will",
  "successionPatrimoineTestamentSubtitle": "CC art. 498–504",
  "successionPatrimoineTestamentBody": "Two valid forms:\n• Holographic: entirely handwritten, dated and signed — no witness required.\n• Notarized: before a notary with 2 witnesses — recommended for complex situations.\nNo will = legal succession by default.",
  "successionPatrimoineDonationTitle": "Lifetime gift",
  "successionPatrimoineDonationSubtitle": "CO art. 239 ff.",
  "successionPatrimoineDonationBody": "Transferring assets during your lifetime allows you to anticipate succession and potentially reduce inheritance tax (varies by canton). Note: gifts are subject to hotchpot if you have forced heirs. The 5 years preceding death are particularly scrutinized.",
  "successionPatrimoineBeneficiairesTitle": "LPP and 3a beneficiaries",
  "successionPatrimoineBeneficiairesSubtitle": "LPP art. 20 · OPP3 art. 2",
  "successionPatrimoineBeneficiairesBody": "LPP capital not converted into annuity and 3a balances are NOT part of your ordinary estate — they are paid to designated beneficiaries. If you designate no one, the legal order applies: married spouse or registered partner, then descendants, then parents. A cohabiting partner must be explicitly designated.",
  "successionPatrimoineDecesProche": "In case of death of a loved one",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase1Timeframe": "D+1 to D+7",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase1Title": "Immediate urgency",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase1Action1": "Declare the death to the civil registry within 2 days",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase1Action2": "Inform the employer and insurances (LAMal, LPP)",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase1Action3": "Block joint bank accounts if necessary",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase1Action4": "Contact the notary if the person had a will",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Timeframe": "D+8 to D+30",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Title": "Administrative procedures",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Action1": "Apply for AVS survivor pensions (LAVS art. 23)",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Action2": "Contact the LPP fund for the death capital",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Action3": "Cancel subscriptions and contracts in the deceased's name",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Action4": "Take inventory of assets and debts",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase2Action5": "Request certificates of inheritance from the notary",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase3Timeframe": "D+31 to D+365",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase3Title": "Legal succession",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase3Action1": "Open succession proceedings with the notary",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase3Action2": "Distribute assets according to the will or law (CC art. 537)",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase3Action3": "File the tax return for the year of death",
  "successionPatrimoinePhase3Action4": "Update the beneficiaries of your own contracts",
  "successionPatrimoineChecklistTitle": "Estate protection checklist",
  "successionPatrimoineChecklist1": "Verify the designation of beneficiaries on each 3a account",
  "successionPatrimoineChecklist2": "Verify the LPP beneficiary designation with your pension fund",
  "successionPatrimoineChecklist3": "Draft or update your will",
  "successionPatrimoineChecklist4": "Check your matrimonial regime if married (CC art. 181 ff.)",
  "successionPatrimoineChecklist5": "Inform your loved ones of the location of your will",
  "successionPatrimoineCtaTitle": "Consult a notary or specialist",
  "successionPatrimoineCtaBody": "A notary or succession law specialist can draft or review your will and guide you on the estate planning suited to your situation.",
  "successionPatrimoineLegalSources": "• CC art. 457–640 — Law of succession\n• CC art. 470–471 — Forced heirship\n• CC art. 498–504 — Forms of will\n• LPP art. 20 — LPP capital beneficiaries\n• OPP3 art. 2 — Pillar 3a beneficiaries",
  "successionPatrimoineDisclaimer": "Educational information, does not constitute legal or estate advice within the meaning of FinSA or the CC. Inheritance rules vary by family situation, matrimonial regime and canton. Consult a notary or succession law specialist for your personal situation.",
